        8ms      5.8     26.5     0.022    8.43   6.58    36.6   [32.5, 52.5, 43.2, 32.3, 36.6]
       12ms      5.3     21.4     0.009    8.53   6.51    32.2   [31.1, 41.5, 35.3, 32.2, 31.2]
       16ms      4.9     19.0     0.139    7.43   6.47    37.5   [33.1, 45.5, 38.0, 37.5, 35.4]
       24ms      4.7     16.8     0.485    6.54   6.46    40.6   [33.3, 43.5, 50.7, 38.0, 40.6]

  PING prediction:  period = fixed_delay + k * tau_GABA   (affine)
  fitted:           period = 27.3 + -0.041 * tau_GABA   (ms)
  slope = -0.041 +/- 0.123   R^2 = 0.018   p = 0.7482
  PRE-REGISTERED CRITERION: slope > 0 AND p < 0.05. Nothing else.

  => CRITERION NOT MET. NOT PING. Whatever this peak is, it is not the
     excitatory-inhibitory loop oscillating, and no claim of emergent
     gamma is warranted -- however many screens it passed.
     Screens reject; only this test confirms.

