  PING prediction:  period = fixed_delay + k * tau_GABA   (affine)
  fitted:           period = 16.8 + 0.760 * tau_GABA   (ms)
  slope = +0.760 +/- 0.113   R^2 = 0.884   p = 0.0005
  PRE-REGISTERED CRITERION: slope > 0 AND p < 0.05. Nothing else.

  => CRITERION MET. The cycle period lengthens with the inhibitory decay
     constant, as PING requires. The peak is a network rhythm generated
     by the E-I loop, and the 17 ms intercept is the fixed part of
     the loop delay (AMPA, membrane, refractory) -- which is why the
     FREQUENCY moves far less than tau does.

========================================================================================
Screens can only reject. This is the only check that can confirm — and it
is the only one that requires re-running the model rather than re-analysing
a spectrum. That is not an inconvenience. That is the point.
