##############################################################################
====================================================================================
E1  NULL OF THE PROMINENCE STATISTIC  (constant-rate Poisson; NO rhythm)
====================================================================================
  200 independent datasets containing NO rhythm whatsoever.
  An unbiased statistic would return ~0 dB. It returns:
      mean    5.62 dB
      sd      0.61 dB
      95th    6.63 dB
      max     7.74 dB

  => Any 'gamma prominence' below ~6.6 dB is not evidence.
     v1 of this preprint reported theta prominence of 6.6-7.5 dB and
     gamma prominence of 11.3-11.9 dB against an implicit null of 0 dB.
        a reported  5.0 dB is exceeded by  88.0% of NO-rhythm data
        a reported  6.9 dB is exceeded by   3.5% of NO-rhythm data
        a reported  7.5 dB is exceeded by   1.0% of NO-rhythm data
        a reported 11.5 dB is exceeded by   0.0% of NO-rhythm data

====================================================================================
E2  THETA HARMONICS MASQUERADING AS GAMMA  (6 Hz drive; gamma depth = 0)
====================================================================================
  Spike trains contain a 6 Hz modulation and NOTHING ELSE.
  Gamma-band content by construction: zero.

   depth  sharp  prom dB   null p    f_pk   k x 6Hz   null says  3 screens say
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
     0.0      1     5.18    0.787    66.3   11x6=66        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.3      1     5.61    0.565    50.4    8x6=48       17% SIG   17% rhythm
     0.6      1     5.25    0.667    40.3    7x6=42        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.9      1     5.52    0.533    45.0    7x6=42        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.9      3     5.35    0.519    56.2    9x6=54        0% sig    0% rhythm
     0.9      6     5.63    0.560    54.7    9x6=54       17% SIG   17% rhythm
     0.9     10     5.28    0.558    47.6    8x6=48        0% sig    0% rhythm

  => At theta depth 0.3, sharpness 1, spike trains with ZERO gamma
     produce 5.6 dB of 'gamma prominence' and the SURROGATE NULL
     calls them significant in 17% of datasets.
     The harmonic screen rejects 83% of them.

  THIS IS THE POINT: a surrogate null is NECESSARY AND NOT SUFFICIENT.
  It asks 'is there non-random fast structure?'. Theta harmonics ARE
  non-random fast structure. They are real. They are not a rhythm.

====================================================================================
E3  THE SCREENS ARE COMPLEMENTARY, NOT REDUNDANT
====================================================================================
  case                        truth   prom      p   f_pk  null  edge  harm  VERDICT
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  no rhythm at all            False   5.62  0.405   61.2    0%    0%    0% rejected  OK
  theta-locked, sigma=5 ms    False   5.69  0.584   33.6    0%    0%    0% rejected  OK
  GROUND-TRUTH 40 Hz gamma     True  28.99  0.000   40.0  100%    0%    0%   RHYTHM  OK
  GROUND-TRUTH 55 Hz gamma     True  23.64  0.000   55.1  100%    0%    0%   RHYTHM  OK

  The theta-locked row is the whole paper: it passes the null, it looks
  like gamma, and only the harmonic screen stops it. The ground-truth row
  proves the screen is not merely destroying everything: a REAL 40 Hz
  rhythm survives all four. Both statements require adequate frequency
  resolution -- at 2.5 s the screen killed the ground-truth rhythm too.

